## Your Task

Identify logical components for the target files above.

For each component, provide:
- `:name` — short kebab-case identifier
- `:summary` — what this component does (1-2 sentences)
- `:purpose` — why it exists
- `:layer` — `:core` | `:subsystem` | `:driver` | `:api` | `:util`
- `:category` — `:backend` | `:frontend` | `:infrastructure` | `:configuration` | `:data` | `:testing` | `:documentation` | `:tooling` | `:shared`
- `:complexity` — `:trivial` | `:simple` | `:moderate` | `:complex` | `:very-complex`
- `:subsystem` — coarser grouping name
- `:files` — list of file paths belonging to this component (ONLY from target files above)
- `:depends-on` — list of component names this depends on (including components you expect in other partitions, based on import edges)

## Rules

- Every target file MUST appear in exactly one component's `:files` list
- Components should contain 2-30 files
- Dependencies based on actual import edges only
- You MAY reference component names from other partitions in `:depends-on` — these will be resolved in a merge step

